HTMLProperty.name: documentation
HTMLProperty.plainTextValue: Compares the information on the availability of the resource with the user's request, and if the resource is available, returns the first available slot. The method is this: the resource object contains the availabile times, so the start of the time window is initially set to the first available time or the first time the user requested, whichever is greater. Then the method gets list of current bookings for the resource, sorted in temporal order, and skips all of the bookings that end before the user's requested time range. When the method finds an existing booking that terminates after the current temporal window, the method checks the start of the existing booking to see if the method can make the requested booking between the start of the time window and the start of the existing booking. If enough free time exists to fit the user in, the method books that time. If not, it sets the start of the time window to the end of the existing booking and goes on to the next booked period. It repeats this process until it can book the resource or it reaches the end of the period in the user request.
